 157, \"to\": 178}, {\"ngram\": \"the Rodchenkov Anti-Doping Act\", \"from\": 251, \"to\": 281}, {\"ngram\": \"an investigation\", \"from\": 297, \"to\": 313}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The decision to launch its own investigation demonstrates that the United States is not only willing to create an extraterritorial enforcement regime against sport corruption, but also has the political will to exercise such powers.\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 386, \"end\": 399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998413759511, \"rank\": 1.586238492792506e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The decision\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 331}, {\"ngram\": \"its own investigation\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 363}, {\"ngram\": \"an extraterritorial enforcement regime\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 468}, {\"ngram\": \"sport corruption\", \"from\": 477, \"to\": 493}, {\"ngram\": \"the political will\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 526}, {\"ngram\": \"such powers\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 550}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The power struggle between the United States, China and the International Olympic Committee threatens to undermine the success of future Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 583, \"end\": 596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998413759511, \"rank\": 1.586238492792506e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 598, \"end\": 603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9998662762424226, \"rank\