"A key limitation\", \"from\": 3635, \"to\": 3651}, {\"ngram\": \"RADA\", \"from\": 3655, \"to\": 3659}, {\"ngram\": \"the requirement\", \"from\": 3663, \"to\": 3678}, {\"ngram\": \"dual criminality\", \"from\": 3683, \"to\": 3699}, {\"ngram\": \"an offence\", \"from\": 3745, \"to\": 3755}, {\"ngram\": \"the laws\", \"from\": 3781, \"to\": 3789}, {\"ngram\": \"the treaty states\", \"from\": 3801, \"to\": 3818}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While RADA criminalises doping conspiracies in the United States, this is relatively new national law and not a common offence globally.\", \"from\": 3821, \"to\": 3957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3872, \"end\": 3885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998413759511, \"rank\": 1.586238492792506e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"RADA\", \"from\": 3827, \"to\": 3831}, {\"ngram\": \"doping conspiracies\", \"from\": 3845, \"to\": 3864}, {\"ngram\": \"relatively new national law\", \"from\": 3895, \"to\": 3922}, {\"ngram\": \"not a common offence\", \"from\": 3927, \"to\": 3947}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Without dual criminality, most officials and organisations like WADA or national sporting organisations tainted by doping scandals can safely ignore this reality - for now.\", \"from\": 3958, \"to\": 4130, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"dual criminality\", \"from\": 3966, \"to\": 3982}, {\"ngram\": \"most officials\", \"from\": 3984, \"to\": 3998}, {\"ngram\": \"organisations\", \"from\": 4003, \"to\": 4016}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 4022, \"to\": 4026}, {\"ngram\": \"national sporting organisations\", \"from\": 4030, \"to\": 4061}, {\"ngram\": \"doping scandals\", \"from\": 4073, \"to\": 4088}, {\"ngram\": \"this reality\", \"from\": 4107, \"to\": 4119}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The next Summer Olympics will be the 2028 Los Angeles games and the IOC has just announcedSalt Lake Cityas the hosts for the 2034 Winter Olympics.\", \"from\": 4132, \"to\": 4278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4174, \"end\": 4185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999997921805, \"rank\": 1.8864406413682338e-10, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 4200, \"end\": 4203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0901012008517738e-40, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The next Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 4132, \"to\": 4156}, {\"ngram\": \"just announcedSalt Lake Cityas\", \"from\": 4208, \"to\": 4238}, {\"ngram\": \"the hosts\", \"from\": 4239, \"to\": 4248}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2034 Winter Olympics\", \"from\": 4253, \"to\": 4277}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Any official of an organisation suspected by the United States of breaching RADA will likely find themselves under the jurisdiction of RADA.\", \"from\": 4279, \"to\": 4419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4328, \"end\": 4341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998413759511, \"rank\": 1.586238492792506e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Any official\", \"from\": 4279, \"to\": 4291}, {\"ngram\": \"an organisation\", \"from\": 4295, \"to\": 4310}, {\"ngram\": \"RADA\", \"from\": 4355, \"to\": 4359}, {\"ngram\": \"the jurisdiction\", \"from\": 4394, \"to\": 4410}, {\"ngram\": \"RADA\", \"from\": 4414, \"to\": 4418}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Salt Lake City Winter Olympics contract comes with a clause to protect WADA.\", \"from\": 4421, \"to\": 4501, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Salt Lake City Winter Olympics contract\", \"from\": 4421, \"to\": 4464}, {\"ngram\": \"a clause\", \"from\": 4476, \"to\": 4484}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 4496, \"to\": 4500}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Language has been added,according to John Coates, Chair of the IOC Legal Affairs Commission to 'protect the integrity of the international anti-doping system'.\", \"from\": 4502, \"to\": 4661, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4539, \"end\": 4550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_H._Coates\", \"score\": 0.9999999999959073, \"rank\": 2.0325974019938572e-12, \"text\": \"John Coates\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_H._Coates\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_H._Coates\"}, {\"begin\": 4565, \"end\": 4568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0901012008517738e-40, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Language\", \"from\": 4502, \"to\": 4510}, {\"ngram\": \"Chair\", \"from\": 4552, \"to\": 4557}, {\"ngram\": \"the integrity\", \"from\": 4606, \"to\": 4619}, {\"ngram\": \"the international anti-doping system\", \"from\": 4623, \"to\": 4659}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nudging local, state or federal lawmakers is not unusual for the IOC.\", \"from\": 4663, \"to\": 4732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4728, \"end\": 4731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0901012008517738e-40, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Nudging local, state or federal lawmakers\", \"from\": 4663, \"to\": 4704}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC providesmodel criminal law against match-fixingand adherence to the WADA code and anti-doping measures are a requirement for host nations as well as individual sports.\", \"from\": 4733, \"to\": 4908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4737, \"end\": 4740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0901012008517738e-40, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"match-fixingand adherence\", \"from\": 4776, \"to\": 4801}, {\"ngram\": \"the WADA code\", \"from\": 4805, \"to\": 4818}, {\"ngram\": \"anti-doping measures\", \"from\": 4823, \"to\": 4843}, {\"ngram\": \"a requirement\", \"from\": 4848, \"to\": 4861}, {\"ngram\": \"host nations\", \"from\": 4866, \"to\": 4878}, {\"ngram\": \"individual sports\", \"from\": 4890, \"to\": 4907}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even Olympic-relatedintellectual propertyrequires legislative safeguards.\", \"from\": 4909, \"to\": 4982, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Even Olympic-relatedintellectual propertyrequires legislative safeguards\", \"from\": 4909, \"to\": 4981}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What we have in effect is a clash between three powerful actors - two nation states and the Olympic movement.\", \"from\": 4984, \"to\": 5093, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"effect\", \"from\": 5000, \"to\": 5006}, {\"ngram\": \"a clash\", \"from\": 5010, \"to\": 5017}, {\"ngram\": \"three powerful actors - two nation states\", \"from\": 5026, \"to\": 5067}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic movement\", \"from\": 5072, \"to\": 5092}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each is concerned with their prestige.\", \"from\": 5094, \"to\": 5132, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their prestige\", \"from\": 5117, \"to\": 5131}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China cannot acknowledge the possibility of systemic doping as was uncovered in the Russian case, while the United Statesrefuses to acknowledgethe possibility of environmental contamination though WADA agreed environmental contamination was reasonable for the positive tests.\", \"from\": 5133, \"to\": 5408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5133, \"end\": 5138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9998662762424226, \"rank\": 6.852075981673668e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 5217, \"end\": 5224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.994255050108737, \"rank\": 0.002943304374053267, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the possibility\", \"from\": 5158, \"to\": 5173}, {\"ngram\": \"systemic doping\", \"from\": 5177, \"to\": 5192}, {\"ngram\": \"the United Statesrefuses\", \"from\": 5237, \"to\": 5261}, {\"ngram\": \"acknowledgethe possibility\", \"from\": 5265, \"to\": 5291}, {\"ngram\": \"environmental contamination\", \"from\": 5295, \"to\": 5322}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 5330, \"to\": 5334}, {\"ngram\": \"environmental contamination\", \"from\": 5342, \"to\": 5369}, {\"ngram\": \"the positive tests\", \"from\": 5389, \"to\": 5407}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC has much to lose if the two most powerful nations in the world cannot compete amicably on the sporting field.\", \"from\": 5410, \"to\": 5527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5414, \"end\": 5417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0901012008517738e-40, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the two most powerful nations\", \"from\": 5438, \"to\": 5467}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 5471, \"to\": 5480}, {\"ngram\": \"the sporting field\", \"from\": 5508, \"to\": 5526}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is difficult to avoid conflating the position of nations given international sport is an exercise insoft power.\", \"from\": 5529, \"to\": 5643, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the position\", \"from\": 5565, \"to\": 5577}, {\"ngram\": \"nations\", \"from\": 5581, \"to\": 5588}, {\"ngram\": \"international sport\", \"from\": 5595, \"to\": 5614}, {\"ngram\": \"an exercise insoft power\", \"from\": 5618, \"to\": 5642}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the US Congress is acting, other nations and their anti-doping agencies will take different positions, with many remaining neutral.\", \"from\": 5644, \"to\": 5781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5654, \"end\": 5665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.300107445712838e-19, \"text\": \"US Congress\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\"}, {\"begin\": 5654, \"end\": 5665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.300107445712838e-19, \"text\": \"US Congress\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other nations\", \"from\": 5677, \"to\": 5690}, {\"ngram\": \"their anti-doping agencies\", \"from\": 5695, \"to\": 5721}, {\"ngram\": \"different positions\", \"from\": 5732, \"to\": 5751}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The strong sporting nations - rich countries who can invest in recreational activities - will have a voice.\", \"from\": 5782, \"to\": 5889, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The strong sporting nations - rich countries\", \"from\": 5782, \"to\": 5826}, {\"ngram\": \"recreational activities\", \"from\": 5845, \"to\": 5868}, {\"ngram\": \"a voice\", \"from\": 5881, \"to\": 5888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This said, such conflicts are principally the politics of sport, rather than that of nations.\", \"from\": 5890, \"to\": 5983, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such conflicts\", \"from\": 5901, \"to\": 5915}, {\"ngram\": \"the politics\", \"from\": 5932, \"to\": 5944}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 5948, \"to\": 5953}, {\"ngram\": \"nations\", \"from\": 5975, \"to\": 5982}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A repeat of the 1980 and 1984 Cold War era boycotts of the Moscow and Los Angeles Olympic Games would be far more damaging today given the rise of Asia in global sports.\", \"from\": 5984, \"to\": 6153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6043, \"end\": 6049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2614277769486579e-14, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}, {\"begin\": 6054, \"end\": 6079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1984_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999854355825087, \"rank\": 1.4564629522380566e-05, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Olympic Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1984_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1984_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A repeat\", \"from\": 5984, \"to\": 5992}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1980 and 1984 Cold War era boycotts\", \"from\": 5996, \"to\": 6035}, {\"ngram\": \"the rise\", \"from\": 6119, \"to\": 6127}, {\"ngram\": \"Asia\", \"from\": 6131, \"to\": 6135}, {\"ngram\": \"global sports\", \"from\": 6139, \"to\": 6152}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adam Masters is Executive Director of the Transnational Research Institute on Corruption at The Australian National University.\", \"from\": 6155, \"to\": 6282, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6247, \"end\": 6281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_National_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Australian National University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_National_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_National_University\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Adam Masters\", \"from\": 6155, \"to\": 6167}, {\"ngram\": \"Executive Director\", \"from\": 6171, \"to\": 6189}, {\"ngram\": \"the Transnational Research Institute\", \"from\": 6193, \"to\": 6229}, {\"ngram\": \"Corruption\", \"from\": 6233, \"to\": 6243}]}, {\"sentence\": \"EAF|China|Will China's doping controversy sink the Olympics?\", \"from\": 6284, \"to\": 6344, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6284, \"end\": 6287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egyptian_Armed_Forces\", \"score\": 0.9999999999131433, \"rank\": 8.591926185775171e-11, \"text\": \"EAF\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egyptian_Armed_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egyptian_Armed_Forces\"}, {\"begin\": 6288, \"end\": 6293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9998662762424226, \"rank\": 6.852075981673668e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 6299, \"end\": 6304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9998662762424226, \"rank\": 6.852075981673668e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6331, \"to\": 6343}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US is hypocrital.\", \"from\": 6346, \"to\": 6367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6350, \"end\": 6352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999793776626, \"rank\": 2.062238571286444e-08, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Its allegations are without real evidence and just exploiting the uncertainties.\", \"from\": 6368, \"to\": 6448, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Its allegations\", \"from\": 6368, \"to\": 6383}, {\"ngram\": \"real evidence\", \"from\": 6396, \"to\": 6409}, {\"ngram\": \"the uncertainties\", \"from\": 6430, \"to\": 6447}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile USADA knew about athletes doping but yet let them off the hook and let them compete without punishment or informing Wada in exchange for ratting in others.\", \"from\": 6449, \"to\": 6614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6459, \"end\": 6464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 6476, \"to\": 6484}, {\"ngram\": \"the hook\", \"from\": 6513, \"to\": 6521}, {\"ngram\": \"pu